Titolo: Jet Set Radio Future

Anno: 2002

Descrizione: Jet Set Radio Future is a 2002 action game developed by Smilebit and published by Sega for the Xbox. The sequel to the Dreamcast game Jet Set Radio that was released in 2000, the player controls members of a street gang that use inline skates to traverse a futuristic Tokyo, spraying graffiti and evading authorities.
Like Jet Set Radio, the game uses a cel-shaded style of animation. Jet Set Radio Future was very well received for its music, art, and gameplay. After the game's initial release, it was bundled with new Xbox consoles with Sega GT 2002 on a dual-game DVD.



Genere: Non specificato


Valutazione: N/A
